properties.areaDesc: West Slopes North Central Cascades and Passes
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 5 at 2:39PM PST until January 5 at 10:00PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Winter Storm Warning above 3000 feet, heavy
snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 3 to 26 inches. For
the Winter Weather Advisory above 2000 feet, snow continued.
Additional snow accumulations of 2 to 4 inches.

* WHERE...Cascade mountains and valleys of Snohomish and King
Counties, including Stevens Pass and Snoqualmie Pass.

* WHEN...For the Winter Storm Warning, from 10 PM this evening
to 4 PM PST Monday. For the Winter Weather Advisory, until 10
PM PST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult to impossible.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snoqualmie Pass will see a change over to
rain Monday morning with snow changing to rain Monday afternoon
at Stevens Pass.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.
